New Cancer Vaccine May Teach Immune System to “See” Malignant Cells
A new cancer vaccine can teach the immune system to “see” the malignant cells and kill them.
As part of the treatment, the vaccine teaches the immune system to recognize malignant cells.
The method requires removing immune cells from a patient and altering them in the laboratory.
Thus, they can "see" a protein common to many cancers and reinject them.
A vaccine trial is generating promising results in patients with different cancers.
