However, the number of people who contract HIV in this way has been reduced in its entirety, Chinese health authorities said at a congress held in Yunnan province.
Every year, the number of people living with HIV and AIDS in China increases by some 100,000.
Sexual transmission of HIV is a serious problem in China’s LGBT community.
Homosexuality was decriminalized in China in 1997, but the LGBT collective suffers a lot of discrimination.
Because of the country’s conservative values, studies have calculated that between 70% and 90% of men who have sex with other men will eventually marry women.
Many of the transmissions of disease are due to not using adequate protection in these relationships.
Since 2003, the Chinese government has pledged universal access to HIV medicines as part of an attempt to address the problem.
